 The lambda keyword is used to define anonymous functions in Python. Usually, such a function is meant for one-time use.
 Syntax
      lambda [arguments] : expression
 Example 1
      >>> sum = lambda x, y, z : x + y + z 
      >>> sum(5, 10, 15)
      30
Example 2
      >>> greet = lambda : print('Hello World!')
      >>> greet()
      Hello World!
